v1.30.8 - SECURITY: PATCH /teams/:teamId via team.edit_details permission (S-22)

The only write site still gated solely by the legacy
requireTeamRole('MANAGER') enum after the v1.23 RBAC migration was
PATCH /api/teams/:teamId. A grep across routes/*.ts confirms it - every
other use of the legacy enum sits on read endpoints (MEMBER, MANAGER)
where the v1.23 permission system doesn't apply.

Fix:
- New permission constant team.edit_details (UI group: Team).
- Migration 20260527180000_team_edit_details_permission backfills the
  new permission onto every existing system Manager role (v1.23/v1.29
  convention) so default behaviour doesn't change.
- routes/teams.ts PATCH /:teamId preHandler migrated from
  [requireTeamRole('MANAGER'), requireScope('admin')] to
  [requireTeamRole('MEMBER','MANAGER'), requirePermission('team.edit_details'),
   requireScope('admin')]. requireTeamRole still runs first to stash
  membership; requirePermission enforces the capability. Global ADMIN
  bypass unchanged.

Regression tests (4 cases in roles.test.ts):
- Custom role granted team.edit_details CAN rename the team
  (before grant: 403; after: 200).
- Custom role WITHOUT it returns 403.
- Default system Manager role CAN rename (migration backfill).
- Global ADMIN still bypasses.

Permission-catalog count 15 -> 16; allPerms helper in roles.test.ts
now lists all 16 constants explicitly (caught a stale-helper drift
where task.manage_dependencies was missing since v1.29).

Verified: tsc clean (backend + frontend). roles.test.ts 14/14. Full
suite 313 passed, 5 skipped (LDAP), 1 pre-existing backups order-flake
(passes in isolation).

Phase boundary: legacy TeamMembership.role enum remains as the v1.23
fallback for null-roleId rows; dropping it is a v1.31+ schema cleanup
flagged in the v1.23 phase boundary.